#' \item{fishSampled: }{Fish Measured (type: NA).
#' The number of fish (or shellfish) measured, e.g. the number of fish for which length or another measure was made from within the sample.}
#' \item{fishSampProb: }{Fish Sampling Probability (type: NA).
#' The sampling probability for the measured fish, this would usually be the ratio of fishTotal/fishSamp and the sample weight, for the measured fish would be the inverse of fishSampProb. These fields are analogous to the sampling probability variables in the SE, TR, and HH and SL tables.}
